review_blob:
On tap at Hopcat 
Aroma: Bubblegum. Fruit juice. Orange. Belgian yeast
Appearance: Unfiltered orange. Not much head
Taste: Barnyard. Spice. Earthy. Sweet. 
Palate: Medium heavy mouth. Creamy. Medium carb
Overall: Tis a Belgian. Great mouthfeel. The unfiltered yeast makes this one special. A great dry trippel.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

On tap at Hopcat
Aroma: Loads of different hop smells. Citrus. Pine.
Appearance: Nice clear red with fluffy white that sticks around. Picture worthy.
Taste: It's an IPA. Spicy floral and citrusy notes. It's the rye that makes this unique. Some caramel. 
Palate: Medium thin body. Medium carb. 
Overall: Unique IPA by the brewery who does them best. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

On tap at Hopcat
Aroma: Coffee. Cocoa.

Taste: Coffee coffee coffee. Hints of cocoa. Bitter finish 
Palate: Heavy mouthfeel. Low carb. 
Overall: Awesome beer for a coffee lover. Reminiscent of breakfast stout. Could drink a few of these
